  "text": "Quantum state redistribution is the following coherent quantum task (see Figure 1) . In this task, Alice, Bob and Referee share a pure state |Φ RABC , with AC belonging to Alice, B to Bob and R to Referee. Alice needs to transfer the register C to Bob, such that the final state Φ ′ RABC satisfies P(Φ ′ RABC , Φ RABC ) ≤ ε, for a given ε ∈ (0, 1) which is the error parameter. Alice and Bob are allowed to have pre-shared entanglement. Furthermore, Bob can perform operations that belong to G. The communication from Alice to Bob is in the form of coherent classical bits [CITATION_1] . We will refer to these as cobits. Fix an ε ∈ (0, 1) ",
